DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       _i_._p_c_a is an image processing program based on the algorithm provided by
       Vali (1990), that processes n (2 >= n) input raster map layers and pro-
       duces n output raster map layers containing the principal components of
       the  input data in decreasing order of variance ("contrast").  The out-
       put raster map layers are assigned names with .1, .2, ... .n  suffixes.
       The   current  geographic  region  definition  and  mask  settings  are
       respected when reading the input raster map layers.  When  the  rescale
       option is used, the output files are rescaled to fit the min,max range.

